What VBA sees here is effectively:

```vb
c.Value = ( "C2" = some_text )
```

That comparison returns `True` or `False`, so every cell gets a Boolean value instead of the postcode with the last 3 characters removed.

You also have two other issues:

1. You're always using `"C2"` / `ws.Range("C2")` instead of the current cell `c`.
